review_blob: Gotta agree with what others have been saying: its not as horrible as I expected, especially for being a malt liquor. Surprisingly smooth. Good carbonation. Definitely better than something like Steel Reserve, which may not be saying much, but there you go.

One of the best beers Ive ever had. I cant say enough good things about it and every time I drink it, Im reminded of how good it really is. It has the perfect amount of carbonation and goes down smooth. I love the banana/citrus aroma and taste.

There should be a way to vote zero; one of the absolute worst beers I have ever had the displeasure of drinking. Yeah, its extremely cheap and will get you drunk quickly, but there are other beers that can accomplish this that dont taste like liquid hell and dont make you want to vomit immediately after consuming them.
